-- Norway Gives 306 Million-Euro Grant to Romania for Clean Energy
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-06-05T10:57:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/norway-gives-306-million-euro-grant-to-romania-for-clean-energy.html
Norway plans to give  Romania  a
financial-assistance grant totaling 306 million euros ($381
million) through 2014 to increase the usage of clean energy in
the country, the Bucharest-based Economy Ministry said.  The Balkan nation can use the money to finance projects
that increase the competitiveness of companies in the renewable
energy field and lower pollution levels, according to an e-
mailed statement from the ministry today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  